com.novartis.opensource.yada.format

Class Joiner

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.novartis.opensource.yada.format.Joiner

  • public class Joiner
extends Object
    Executes on-the-fly joins of result sets from multiple queries. For the moment, only supports delimited and shallow JSON results. (Isn't that enough?!)
    Since:
    0.6.2.0
    Author:
    Dave Varon

    • Method Detail

      • join

        public Object join()
        The meaty bit. Uses hsqld to create in memory db tables for the combined rows of converted results in each yqr. Then uses the join spec to build data structures, mapping columns to tables, tables to columns, and table pairs to columns. Then builds a select join query from the structures, executes it, wraps and returns the results.
        Returns:
        a JSONArray containing structured results, or a StringBuffer containing delimited results
